                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1035">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.628/136: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 29, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>186. Your 208, November 12, 5 p.m. On November 27, the Department discussed the
                    matter orally with the Japanese Ambassador,<note n="66" xml:id="d1035fn66">See
                        section II of memorandum dated November 27, <ref target="#pg_1020">p.
                            1020</ref>.</note> who stated that he would lay before his Government
                    our view in regard to the desirability of there being concluded a
                    convention.</p>
                <p>Please take no further action pending the receipt of the instruction which the
                    Department will expect to send you as soon as a reply will have been made by the
                    Japanese Ambassador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
